'''宏觀演化'''（{{lang-en|Macroevolution}}），又譯'''宏演化'''、'''巨觀演化'''、'''巨演化'''、'''大演化'''、'''廣演化'''、'''廣進化'''，是在物種水準或以上的尺度上的[[演化|演化]]，與[[微演化|微觀演化]]不同<ref>{{Cite book |author=Dobzhansky, Theodosius Grigorievich |authorlink=Theodosius Dobzhansky |title=Genetics and the origin of species |location=New York |publisher=Columbia Univ. Press |year=1937 |page=12|lccn=37033383}}</ref>，宏觀演化指的是物種或種群內[[等位基因頻率|等位基因頻率]]的較小進化變化<ref name=Reznick>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Reznick DN, Ricklefs RE |title=Darwin's bridge between microevolution and macroevolution |journal=Nature |volume=457 |issue=7231 |pages=837–42 |date=February 2009 |pmid=19212402 |doi=10.1038/nature07894}}</ref>。宏觀演化和微觀演化在不同的時間尺度上描述了基本相同的過程<ref>{{cite book |authors=Matzke, Nicholas J. and Gross, Paul R. |year=2006 |chapter=Analyzing Critical Analysis: The Fallback Antievolutionist Strategy |editors=[[Eugenie_Scott|Eugenie Scott]] and [[Glenn_Branch|Glenn Branch]] |title=Not in Our Classrooms: Why Intelligent Design is Wrong for Our Schools |publisher=Beacon Press |location=Boston |isbn=0-80-703278-6 |pages=28–56 |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=Pr-ZJPcXAvsC |ref=Matzke |access-date=2018-11-15 |archive-date=2018-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115112918/https://books.google.ca/books?id=Pr-ZJPcXAvsC |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=futu>{{cite book |first=Douglas |last=Futuyma |title=Evolutionary Biology |url=https://archive.org/details/evolutionarybiol0000futu_v2j4 |publisher=Sinauer Associates |year=1998 |page=[https://archive.org/details/evolutionarybiol0000futu_v2j4/page/25 25] |isbn=0-87893-189-9}}</ref> 。

[[物種形成|物種形成]]的過程可能屬於兩者的範圍，取決於驅動它的力量。 [[古生物學|古生物學]]，[[演化發育生物學|演化發育生物學]]，[[比較基因組學|比較基因組學]]，和{{le|基因組學的地層學|Genomic phylostratigraphy}}，為宏觀演化的模式和過程提供了大部分證據<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coursehero.com/file/p49lji/Maintained-gene-flow-between-two-populations-can-also-lead-to-a-combination-of/|title=Maintained gene flow between two populations can also lead to a combination of|website=www.coursehero.com|language=en|access-date=2018-09-12|archive-date=2018-09-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180913002230/https://www.coursehero.com/file/p49lji/Maintained-gene-flow-between-two-populations-can-also-lead-to-a-combination-of/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

